90
00:06:11,920 --> 00:06:13,279
Nurse Gao lives in the county town.

91
00:06:13,480 --> 00:06:14,199
This room

92
00:06:14,199 --> 00:06:16,079
is the one she uses when she works late or night shifts.

93
00:06:16,680 --> 00:06:17,680
She rarely sleeps here.

94
00:06:18,319 --> 00:06:19,160
The things on the bed

95
00:06:19,240 --> 00:06:20,199
were already changed by her yesterday.

96
00:06:20,199 --> 00:06:21,199
Everything is clean.

97
00:06:21,600 --> 00:06:23,079
Hotels in the county town are really expensive.

98
00:06:24,199 --> 00:06:25,480
We really have to thank her.

99
00:06:31,519 --> 00:06:32,519
You've had a long day too.

100
00:06:32,920 --> 00:06:33,720
Get some rest early.

101
00:06:34,160 --> 00:06:35,120
I'll sleep on the floor.

102
00:06:35,399 --> 00:06:36,600
Let me sleep on the floor.

103
00:06:37,399 --> 00:06:38,480
You're the patient.

104
00:06:39,079 --> 00:06:39,920
That won't do.

105
00:06:41,160 --> 00:06:42,199
Why not?

106
00:06:43,399 --> 00:06:44,800
I'm here to take care of you.

107
00:06:45,759 --> 00:06:47,120
So I should be the one to sleep on the floor.

108
00:06:47,800 --> 00:06:48,680
Besides,

109
00:06:50,079 --> 00:06:51,319
if I get up at night,

110
00:06:51,720 --> 00:06:52,920
it'll be easier to look after you.

111
00:06:53,600 --> 00:06:55,600
You make me sound like I'm seventy or eighty years old.

112
00:06:55,959 --> 00:06:57,000
If you sleep on the floor,

113
00:06:57,120 --> 00:06:58,240
then I just won't sleep at all.

114
00:07:10,720 --> 00:07:11,560
You...

115
00:07:12,319 --> 00:07:13,639
Stay with me a little longer.

116
00:07:24,560 --> 00:07:26,240
You've read a lot of novels, right?

117
00:07:29,600 --> 00:07:31,120
Is it true that in every story

118
00:07:31,920 --> 00:07:32,920
there's always love?

119
00:07:35,879 --> 00:07:36,839
Most of them do.

120
00:07:39,839 --> 00:07:41,240
Are the things they write about real?

121
00:07:47,399 --> 00:07:48,399
I guess so.

122
00:07:53,399 --> 00:07:54,439
The books say

123
00:07:55,560 --> 00:07:56,800
when lovers kiss,

124
00:07:57,680 --> 00:07:58,839
it's always sweet.

125
00:08:01,959 --> 00:08:03,040
I want to try it.

126
00:08:28,600 --> 00:08:29,439
It's bitter.

127
00:08:30,439 --> 00:08:31,839
It smells like disinfectant.

128
00:08:32,360 --> 00:08:33,840
Do you really have to do everything

129
00:08:34,480 --> 00:08:35,879
that the novel describes?

130
00:08:39,360 --> 00:08:40,799
The lovers in the novel,

131
00:08:41,879 --> 00:08:42,919
do they all

132
00:08:43,639 --> 00:08:46,240
embrace each other naked?

133
00:08:49,519 --> 00:08:50,799
I don't really remember.

134
00:09:24,480 --> 00:09:25,480
What happened next

135
00:09:26,360 --> 00:09:27,639
wasn't written in the novel.

136
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:30,039
Do you know?

137
00:09:30,679 --> 00:09:31,480
Yeah.

138
00:09:33,519 --> 00:09:34,799
They were just like us,

139
00:09:36,120 --> 00:09:37,120
holding each other

140
00:09:38,840 --> 00:09:39,639
as they fell asleep.

141
00:09:41,039 --> 00:09:42,200
When they woke up,

142
00:09:43,960 --> 00:09:45,639
they lived a happy life.
